{
  "stem": "3804.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When she didn't write anymore, we didn't hear from her, we-- we understood that she's dead.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It never-- There's no way.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, for years and years, you don't hear anything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the real thing, I've heard, is-- is here in the United States.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's really kind of something that you couldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I-- I-- when I-- all the story, when it was closed and all this, and captured Eichmann, everything and all this, also finished about 30 years that I can write my book, I said I have to know one thing.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Where we lived, I couldn't remember the name, Zolkiewka, because if I would hear it, I would know.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Nobody could remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was nobody to ask because everybody was dead.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And also, I didn't know the fate of my sister, Fruma.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Dedicated her to the book.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And suddenly, one day in-- near the Lexington Hotel, maybe, you know, it's in the 48th Street.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The was with me a professor, Chaim Shaket, from Miami, he sits-- he's standing right there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I throw my jacket.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We have to go on a shuttle to-- to Washington.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I threw my jacket in-- into the car, and said, let's take this car.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He said, why this car?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I said, I don't know, I throw my jacket in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I went to the Lexington, up to the hotel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Brought my-- my suitcase.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So then you see, it's always written the names of the-- of the driver.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I see a Jewish name, Abraham, or something like this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I said to him, you Jewish?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He said, you don't see my name there?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I said, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Maybe we talked like this, and I say, you-- you're familiar maybe with the name [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Milchman? ?] You know, our first name?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He said what do you mean familiar?",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
